  "clinical_criteria": [
    "Oral ulcer: 2 inclusion codes on at least 2 separate days",
    "Arthritis: 2 inclusion codes on at least 2 separate days",
    "Serositis: 2 inclusion codes on at least 2 separate days",
    "Acute Cutaneous Lupus: 2 inclusion codes on at least 2 separate days OR medications (Plaquenil/hydrochloroquine) AND rash codes",
    "Chronic Cutaneous Lupus: 2 inclusion codes on at least 2 separate days",
    "Proteinuria: >500mg (LOINC 2889-4, 21482-5)",
    "Red blood cell casts: >0/hpf (LOINC 51790-4, 33804-6, 5807-3)",
    "Thrombocytopenia: platelet count < 100K/uL",
    "Leukopenia: lymphocyte count <1.5 K/uL or WBC <4 K/uL",
    "Hemolytic Anemia: (low hemoglobin <8 g/dl AND high LDH >2x normal) OR (high reticulocytes >3% AND high LDH >2x normal)",
    "ANA: titer >=1:80 or positive result or >=8 IU/mL",
    "Anti-dsDNA: titer >1:10 or positive result or >5 IU/mL",
    "Anti-Smith: titer >=1:80 or positive result or >=20",
    "Antiphospholipid antibodies: >20 G/MPL or >20 U/ml or positive/reactive results with specific combinations",
    "Low complement C3: <70 mg/dL (or <80 mg/dL depending on site)",
    "Low complement C4: <9 mg/dL (or <11 mg/dL depending on site)",
    "Direct Coombs test: positive result",
    "Exclusion criteria: various codes that exclude patients from each criterion",
    "Temporal exclusions: some exclusion codes only apply if found within 7 days of inclusion codes"
  ],
  "algorithm_summary": "The SLE phenotype algorithm uses SLICC (Systemic Lupus International Collaborating Clinics) criteria to identify patients with Systemic Lupus Erythematosus. To have SLE according to SLICC, a patient must have: 1) at least four criteria, with at least one clinical criterion AND one immunologic criterion, OR 2) have biopsy proven lupus nephritis as the sole clinical criterion in the presence of ANA or anti-dsDNA antibodies. The algorithm evaluates 11 clinical criteria (oral ulcer, alopecia, neurological, arthritis, serositis, acute cutaneous lupus, chronic cutaneous lupus, renal) and 6 immunologic criteria (thrombocytopenia, leukopenia, hemolytic anemia, antinuclear antibodies, anti-dsDNA, antiphospholipid antibodies, anti-Smith antibodies, low complement, direct Coombs test). Each criterion requires specific diagnosis codes, laboratory values, or medication combinations, with many requiring codes on multiple separate dates. The algorithm includes both inclusion and exclusion criteria, with some exclusions only applying if found within 7 days of inclusion codes. Version 5.4 adds natural language processing (NLP) for arthritis and renal criteria to improve detection from clinical notes.",
  "analysis_timestamp": "2026-01-29T04:00:08.542196Z"
}